b. a pH-heterogeneous edible ink-image disposed on an upper surface of the edible substrate, the ink-image comprising a first and second set of ink-dots, wherein:
i. for each given ink-dot of both the first and second sets of ink-dots, a primary colorant thereof is an extract of plant matter or solids of the extract of the plant matter, wherein a color of the extract of plant matter or solids of the extract of the plant matter is pH sensitive;
ii. for each given ink-dot of the first sets of ink-dots, a pH thereof is within 0.5 or within 1 or within 1.5 of a common first pH value and a color thereof is a first dot-color;
